snippet.title: Dhanda Nyoliwala - Not Guilty (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
‚ÄúNot Guilty‚Äù is the Tenth song from Dhanda Nyoliwala‚Äôs album. The track reflects real-life struggles, false blame, loyalty, and inner strength. With powerful Haryanvi lyrics, Dhanda talks about standing firm when the whole world is against you. Raw emotions, street reality, and faith in family make this song deeply relatable.

snippet.title: Rishtey (Official Music Video) | Jass Bajwa | Punjabi Song 2026
snippet.description:
Jass Bajwa presents the official music video of Rishtey. It is a touching Punjabi song that shows the deep bond between a daughter and her family. As she gets ready to leave her parents‚Äô home after marriage, memories of childhood, siblings, and family moments come rushing back.

The song captures her love, fear, and pain of leaving the house where she grew up. She remembers small fights, shared laughter, and the comfort of seeing her parents every day. Before starting her new life, she makes emotional requests to her brother and sister, showing how strongly she is connected to her family. Rishtey beautifully reflects love, memories, and the strength it takes to move forward while keeping family close to the heart.

snippet.title: üî¥ INDIA VS NEW ZEALAND LIVE MATCH | IND VS NZ 1ST ODI 2026 | LIVE CRICKET MATCH SCORES, 1ST INNINGS
snippet.description:
üî¥ INDIA VS NEW ZEALAND LIVE MATCH | IND VS NZ 1ST ODI 2026 | LIVE CRICKET MATCH SCORES, 1ST INNINGS

For Contact Umerhafeez2022@gmail.com

Topics to be covered in the live stream üëáüèº

IND Vs NZ 1st ODI Live 
IND vs NZ Live Match Today 
India vs New Zealand Live
Live Cricket Match Today 
Cricket Live Match



When: Sunday, January 11, 2026 at 1:30 PM local time

Where:VCA Stadium, Vadodara

What to expect: Perfect, friendly weather to begin with means a full match is assured. The pitch is a batter's paradise, and a high-scoring contest is on the cards - unless, of course, one side suffers a collapse. After India vs New Zealand Series, India have to go to the ICC Men's T20 Cricket World Cup 2026. The most awaiting contest India vs Pakistan T20 Cricket World Cup will be played on February 15 2026. IND vs PAK matches are always full of thrilling moments. The rivalry on its peak.

Team News

India: With Shubman Gill back at the helm, he will naturally take back his place at the top of the order, a move that could confine Yashasvi Jaiswal to the bench. With Mohammed Siraj in the mix, accommodating three specialist pacers will not be easy - meaning one of Prasidh Krishna or Harshit Rana is likely to miss out. It will also be interesting to see whether there is room for all-rounder Nitish Reddy. With Ravindra Jadeja a certainty, the final spot in the XI could come down to a choice between Kuldeep Yadav and Washington Sundar.

Probable XI: Shubman Gill (C), Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, KL Rahul (WK), Shreyas Iyer (VC), Ravindra Jadeja, Nitish Kumar Reddy, Harshit Rana, Kuldeep Yadav, Mohammed Siraj, Arshdeep Singh.

New Zealand: With Kane Williamson, Mitchell Santner, Tom Latham, Rachin Ravindra and Jacob Duffy out of the squad, it is largely a second-string ODI side under Michael Bracewell. However, the New Zealanders are coming off three successive series wins against Pakistan, England and the West Indies respectively, and Shubman Gill's side would take them lightly only at their peril.

Probable XI: Devon Conway (wk), Will Young, Henry Nicholls, Daryl Mitchell, Glenn Phillips, Michael Bracewell (c), Josh Clarkson, Kristian Clarke, Kyle Jamieson, Aditya Ashok, Michael Rae.

Cricket Live Match



When: Sunday, January 11, 2026 at 1:30 PM local time

Where:VCA Stadium, Vadodara

What to expect: Perfect, friendly weather to begin with means a full match is assured. The pitch is a batter's paradise, and a high-scoring contest is on the cards - unless, of course, one side suffers a collapse. After India vs New Zealand Series, India have to go to the ICC Men's T20 Cricket World Cup 2026. The most awaiting contest India vs Pakistan T20 Cricket World Cup will be played on February 15 2026. IND vs PAK matches are always full of thrilling moments. The rivalry on its peak.

Team News

India: With Shubman Gill back at the helm, he will naturally take back his place at the top of the order, a move that could confine Yashasvi Jaiswal to the bench. With Mohammed Siraj in the mix, accommodating three specialist pacers will not be easy - meaning one of Prasidh Krishna or Harshit Rana is likely to miss out. It will also be interesting to see whether there is room for all-rounder Nitish Reddy. With Ravindra Jadeja a certainty, the final spot in the XI could come down to a choice between Kuldeep Yadav and Washington Sundar.

Probable XI: Shubman Gill (C), Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, KL Rahul (WK), Shreyas Iyer (VC), Ravindra Jadeja, Nitish Kumar Reddy, Harshit Rana, Kuldeep Yadav, Mohammed Siraj, Arshdeep Singh.

New Zealand: With Kane Williamson, Mitchell Santner, Tom Latham, Rachin Ravindra and Jacob Duffy out of the squad, it is largely a second-string ODI side under Michael Bracewell. However, the New Zealanders are coming off three successive series wins against Pakistan, England and the West Indies respectively, and Shubman Gill's side would take them lightly only at their peril.

Probable XI: Devon Conway (wk), Will Young, Henry Nicholls, Daryl Mitchell, Glenn Phillips, Michael Bracewell (c), Josh Clarkson, Kristian Clarke, Kyle Jamieson, Aditya Ashok, Michael Rae.

snippet.title: HAHI THOKA TUMAR DUSOKU (Music Video) - Krishnamoni Chutia | Rangdhali 2026 | Kamalika Kashyap
snippet.description:
Make reels on this song: https://www.instagram.com/reels/audio/1240613301265940?igsh=MTk2azR1eGVneXVnYQ==

‚ÄúHahi Thoka Tumar Dusoku‚Äù is the title track of the album Rangdhali 2026, sung by Krishnamoni Chutia and Kamalika Kashyap, the song blends energetic folk arrangements with heartfelt lyrics, making it a true representation of the "Rangdhali" musical legacy. With rich use of traditional instruments like dhol, bahi, tabla, percussion, and modern production finesse, this title track sets the tone for the entire "Rangdhali 2026" album.
